# Arduino Multi-Sensor Alarm Clock

This project is an Arduino-based alarm clock system developed as part of a programming course. It utilizes real-time clock (RTC) modules and environmental sensors to provide timekeeping and monitoring functionality.

## Features
* **Real-Time Clock (RTC):** Accurate time tracking using the Makuna/RTC library.
* **Environmental Monitoring:** Temperature and humidity tracking using the DHT sensor library.
* **Display Interface:** Real-time data visualization via an I2C LCD display.
* **Modular Code Structure:** Organized with specialized wrappers for sensors and hardware components.

## Tech Stack
* **Language:** C++
* **Platform:** PlatformIO (Arduino framework)
* **Hardware:**
  * Arduino Uno
  * DHT Sensor
  * I2C LCD Module
  * RTC Module

## Project Structure
* `/src`: Main application logic.
* `/lib`: Custom wrappers for hardware components (`sensors.h`, `lcd_wrapper.h`, `rtc_wrapper.h`).
* `platformio.ini`: Configuration file for dependencies and build settings.

## Getting Started
1. Clone this repository.
2. Open the folder in VS Code with the PlatformIO extension installed.
3. PlatformIO will automatically install the necessary libraries defined in `platformio.ini` (Makuna/RTC, DHT sensor library, etc.).
4. Build and upload the code to your Arduino Uno board.

